Data1 Analysis¶

Wu Dayu(PB19030934) and Jin Xiaolong(PB19000314)

Project background: Internet of Vehicles data, In simple terms, the data is vehicle-related data recorded by on-board equipment: including real-time driving speed, acceleration, fuel consumption, engine speed, etc. Through the statistical analysis of Internet of Vehicles data, it can bring certain value to insurance companies, car manufacturers and driving drivers. The data provides Internet of Vehicles data for a trival of a car.The data includes time(TIME), longitude(LONG) ,latitude(LAT) ,fuel consumption (CONSUM),acceleration(LONGACC) ,speed(SPEED) ,engine speed(WHEEL) ,cumulative distance.

Descriptive Statistics and Analysis¶

In [21]:
# import package
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# load data
df1 = pd.read_csv("data1.csv") 
num = len(df1)

# time
df1["TIME_1s"]=pd.date_range(start='2016-11-11 19:50', periods=num,freq="S")
df1.set_index("TIME_1s")

# observe the trend of data over time


df1.plot(x="TIME_1s",y="LONGACC",title='Time and Acceleration',xlabel="Time",ylabel="Acceleration")

df1.plot(x="TIME_1s",y="SPEED",title='Time and Speed',xlabel="Time",ylabel="Speed")

df1.plot(x="TIME_1s",y="CONSUM",title='Time and Fuel Consumption',xlabel="Time",ylabel="Fuel Consumption")

df1.plot(x="TIME_1s",y="WHEEL",title='Time and Engine Speed',xlabel="Time",ylabel="Engine Speed")

df1.plot(x="TIME_1s",y="CUMDIS",title='Time and Cumulative Distance',xlabel="Time",ylabel="Cumulative Distance")
Out[21]:
<AxesSubplot:title={'center':'Time and Cumulative Distance'}, xlabel='Time', ylabel='Cumulative Distance'>

  1. From the time series chart of vehicle acceleration, When the acceleration is greater than 0, the car is accelerating. When the acceleration is 0, the car is decelerating. In a certain period of time, the acceleration is equal to 0, and the car is moving almost at a constant speed. The maximum acceleration of the car is about $8 m/s^2$, which means that the car brakes from a speed of about $30 km/h$ within $ 1s$. The vehicle has encountered a sudden brake, and may have encountered an accident

  2. From the time series chart of vehicle speed, the speed changes greatly. The car may decelerate and stop several times during this period and start again.And the top speed exceeds $80 km/h$ ,so he may be speeding and violate traffic rules.

  3. From the time series chart of fuel consumption, the consumption changes greatly.

  4. From the time series chart of engine speed, the speed also changes greatly. But the engine speed change trend and the speed change trend are roughly the same.

  5. From the time series chart of Cumulative Distance, obviously ,due to the limitation of data collection, the accumulated distance changes periodically over time

# V_t+1
speed_1 =  df1["SPEED"][1:num]

# Speed change before and after
plt.scatter(df1["SPEED"][0:(num-1)],speed_1)
plt.xlabel("$V_t$")
plt.ylabel("$V_(t+1)$")
plt.title("Speed change before and after")
Out[23]:
Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Speed change before and after')

Plot the speed scatter plot before and after the measurement time, we can analyze the driving stability of the car owner.If the speed difference between the front and the rear is too large and it is not on the overall regression line, it means that the speed of the car is changing drastically at this time.

If there are too many outliers, it means that the driver's driving habits are not good, and they often stop and speed up quickly, which is dangerous. Therefore, the price of insurance for the driver should be increased.

This also reflects that the drivers driving habits are not good

From the boxplot comparison of rushhour, the mean value of the fuel consumption is 7.56. The data of the fuel consumption has no outliers.

From the boxplot comparison of rushhour, the mean value of the acceleration is -0.422438the variance of the acceleration is large. In addition, there are many outliers in the data and they are widely distributed. Therefore, it shows from the side that the driver often stops and starts quickly while driving, and the drive is not stable enough, and the driving habits may be bad.

From the boxplot comparison of speed, the mean value of the speed is 32.740143. The data of the speed has no outliers.

From the boxplot comparison of engine speed, the mean value of the speed is 32.740143. The data of the speed has no outliers.

After visualizing the map data,we find that the path on the map is not completely overlap with the existing road. This may be because data collectors need to desensitize the GPS data of the vehicle due to user privacy considerations, but the approximate location will not have too much difference.Therefore, we can analyze the driving behavior of the owner from the road conditions and geographic information around the route.

Besides this, we find that the data collection point was near the railway station in Bayuquan District, Yingkou City, Liaoning Province.The area is remote, beside the highway section. We speculate that the owner is driving along Bincheng Avenue to Xiongyuehe Road to Xiongyue Town.We note that Xiongyuehe Road is a branch of National Highway G228.

Therefore, the car is faster, but it should be combined with the geographical background to make a further analysis of the drivers driving behavior.
